    \item Republican Party, with 230 or more representatives. Probability=\Sexpr{q4}\%
    \item Republican Party, with less than 230 representatives. Probability=\Sexpr{q3}\%
\end{itemize}

This  means that the probability that the Democrats win the House is \Sexpr{q1+q2}\% and this is the value I use for the general question.

